    1872 describe('edge cases', () => {
    1873
    describe('bombarding the store with near-parallel upserts', () => {
    1874 //
    1875 // NOTE: WARNING: Chances are, in order to pass this test, you
    1876 // need to create a unique index on the users.email column/field,
    1877 // - whether you are testing a plugin meant for a SQL or a NoSQL
    1878 // database/store.
    1879 //
    1880 // That's due to the way how upserts are normally implemented in
    1881 // databases.
    1882 //
    1883 // For example, in case of MongoDb, in order for the database to
    1884 // be able to avert race conditions, a field you upsert on must
    1885 // have a unique index created on it. Without the index, your
    1886 // upserts will not be atomic, and as a result your plugin will
    1887 // fail the race condition tests.
    1888 //
    1889 // It is a case of a leaky abstraction that test suites of client
    1890 // store plugins must "know" what collection and what field is
    1891 // being used in a race condition test in seneca-store-test. We
    1892 // may want to come up with a better alternative in the future.
    1893 //
    1894
    describe('1 upsert$ field', () => {
    1895
    it('does not result in a race condition - creates a single new entity', (fin) => {
    1896
    si.test(fin)
    1897
    1898 const user_entity = si.entity('users')
    1899
    1900 const upsertUser = (cb) =>
    1901
    user_entity
    1902 .data$({
    1903 username: 'jimihendrix',
    1904 email: 'jimi@experience.com',
    1905 })
    1906
    .save$({ upsert$: ['email'] }, cb)
    1907
    1908 Async.parallel([upsertUser, upsertUser, upsertUser], (err) => {
    1909
    if (err) {
    1910 return fin(err)
    1911
    }
    1912
    1913 user_entity.list$((err, users) => {
    1914
    if (err) {
    1915 return fin(err)
    1916
    }
    1917
    1918 expect(users.length).to.equal(1)
    1919
    1920 expect(users[0]).to.contain({
    1921 username: 'jimihendrix',
    1922 email: 'jimi@experience.com',
    1923 })
    1924
    1925 return fin()
    1926 })
    1927 })
    1928
    1929 return
    1930
    })
    1931
    })
    1932
    })
    1933 })
    1934 })
    1935
    1936 describe('edge cases', () => {

    397 return function it(name, opts, func) {
    398
    if ('function' === typeof opts) {
    399 func = opts
    400 opts = {}
    401
    }

    404 name,
    405 opts,

    func(fin)
